The DA announced on Tuesday that Patricia de Lille has ceased to be a member of the party, thereby ending her seven-year rule as Mayor of Cape Town Natasha Mazzone, the Deputy Chairwoman of the DA’s federal council, told a media briefing the “cessation of her membership” was based on the fact that De Lille breached the party’s constitution by declaring her readiness to resign on a radio talk show. READ MORE: I fear no-one but my God – De Lille ahead of internal DA motion